Introduction

Aom is a Thai singer, actor and trainee under Escrow Entertainment.

On November 8, 2021, he was introduced as a contestant on World Star's survival show Boyband The Series. He ranked 10th place overall, making him a member of the winning group XI. Aom debuted with the group on August 29, 2022, with the release of the digital single "Flame".

He made his acting debut with a supporting role in GMM 25's Thai series "Boyband", which aired from February 16 to March 23, 2023.

Aom announced on his SNS that he had left World Star Academy on October 29, 2023, even tho the agency claimed otherwise the next day. However, as he has not been active with them since then, he is believed to have left the group and the company.

On September 26, 2024, he was revealed as a contestant on JTBC's survival show PROJECT7 starting in October 2024.
